Functionally, it is perfect, but it certainly isn't pretty.The case colors show some very light pitting, and a little staining from the rust that used to be there.This was made by marlin after they purchased nef/H&R, and is the same as an h&r topper, so parts can be found everywhere. The only reason I'm selling it is because it made me very fond of the .410 cartridge, and so I went out and bought a very nice O/U, and will likely not use this one for much anymore.Makes a great hunting gun, locks up tight, clean bore, functionally perfect. Make an offer. 419-371-8six80

postcontent: David Miller Co. custom hunting rifle, built by arguably the finest rifle maker in America today. This “Marksman” model is built in 300 Weatherby Magnum caliber, serial number DM-G53 with a 26” fluted barrel. The caliber and the maker’s name, David Miller Co., are marked on the barrel about mid-point and the serial number on the top flat. Built around Miller’s Winchester style action, Model 70 style safety and bolt release and Miller’s custom hinged floor plate and trigger guard with the caliber on the floor plate. The receiver holds Miller’s rugged custom one-piece scope base and rings. The rifle is mounted in a beautiful laminated stock with an ebony forend and grip cap, a classic European style cheek piece, with a hand rubbed satin oil finish. The rifle also comes with a Bansner Sheep Hunter fiberglass/carbon stock, bedded and pillar posted around the guns action. The action screws have Miller’s custom Allen screw head, engraved with a six petal flower. The stock also has Miller’s custom, lightly engraved, sling swivel bases and an initial plate on the bottom of the stock. The length of pull is 14 inches over a solid red recoil pad. The rifle holds a Leopold Vari-X 6.5-20X scope, 30mm tube with Precision Reticle stadia lines. The rifle shoots less than .30 MOA with handloads at 100 yards. This rifle is in extremely fine condition and has only been test fired. The rifle retains virtually all of its custom finish to both metal and wood. The stock has one or two tiny handling marks and the action is crisp and the bore is bright and shiny.
